A man collapsed and died on Monday in Kiambu town while he was taking tea and chapati. Eyewitnesses said the man only identified as Kawoiro was shivering. He was offered tea, sat down at the wall of Kiambu Level Five Hospital before collapsing. “I saw Kawoiro in the morning, he was shivering and looked weak. I urged him to seek treatment but I left him at the hospital entrance,”  resident Francis Kimani said. Kimani said afterwards, he found the man lying on the ground but looked lifeless. “There is a makeshift seat between Kiambu hospital and Kiambu law courts that is where I found Kawoiro,” he said. Ann Njoki a hawker said the man fell from a makeshift seat near the hospital and no one went to his aid and after a while, people surrounded him because he was motionless. “People were just looking at him, he was not breathing,”  Njoki said. Police officers from the Kiambu police station arrived at the scene where they found chapati in his pocket. The officers took the man to Kiambu hospital where he was pronounced dead and taken to the mortuary Family members said he had fled his home in Tinganga village many years ago and was a carpenter before engaging himself in washing car headlights in Kiambu town. Edited by Kiilu Damaris